NIA CO-PROCESSOR

This report presents the design, implementation, and verification of a Neural Inference Accelerator (NIA) co-processor integrated into the StarCore-1 processor. The NIA targets the multiply-accumulate (MAC) operation central to neural network inference, using 16-bit fixed-point arithmetic in Q8.8 format with a 40-bit accumulator. Two multiplier architectures are evaluated: P1, based on a 4:2 compressor-based adder, and P2, based on a carry-select adder. Both variants are integrated through a six-state Mealy FSM controller and an add-accumulator datapath featuring Parametric ReLU (PReLU) activation. The NIA interfaces with the processor exclusively through a memory-mapped I/O extension, requiring no pipeline modifications. Post-synthesis results show that P1 achieves a 2.56× higher maximum frequency (2845 MHz vs. 1110 MHz) while P2 is more area- and power-efficient. All functional test cases, including full CPU pipeline integration, passed successfully.
